      },
      "date": "2012-01-06 00:52:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(3 inline comments)\n\nIf the default is to create multiple OI files then we definitely need to have an OBD_INCOMPAT flag to prevent problems if someone tries to downgrade.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "09a960833ef0370d13add8d43930c845fcfebe1d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-06 14:14:55.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 4.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "b58a53f5a30b476818e5028037c5bfc5be1dd4e7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-06 15:03:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe situation is some trouble, as following:\n\n1) new MDT mount up on new disk, and creates a series of \"oi.16.N\" files.\n\n2) new MDT umount\n\n3) old MDT mount on new disk, firstly, it will create old \"oi.16\" file by:\nmdt_init0() => mdt_stack_init() => ldo_prepare() => osd_oi_init().\n\nAnd then the mount will fail at:\nmdt_init0() => mdt_fs_setup() => mdt_server_data_init().\n\nAlthough you prevent old MDT mount up on new disk, it leaves an unused old \"oi.16\" file on the new disk.\n\n4) new MDT mount on new disk again, it will find the old \"oi.16.\" file created by last old MDT mount, so it will regard the new disk as old one. That is not what we expected.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "7e02b6fb835bfcd59f3bcf65c9e97e6391aa2aae",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-06 15:10:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nBuild Started http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/4129/ ",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "0cd58f778cf25a1f83c3d0d0f8f395ba63953f66",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-06 15:39:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Verified\n\nBuild Successful \n \nhttp://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/4129/ : SUCCESS",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "710334d5f02f0d8085314b9968b1b5b3f0ebaf99",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-06 15:39:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nI've discussed with Fanyong, and we think there is no easy fix for it, the clean solution would be like Andreas said, we should check/set these flags in OSD instead of MDT, but it will take more efforts and code changes and we probably can do this in the future. I think if we want multiple-OI then earlier is better and less trouble in the future,  there is a workaround for now: we can check new OI files before old single OI file, so even there is garbage left on disk(as Fanyong said), we will just ignore it. Again, it's not the final solution and it's tricky, but it can work at least.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "be8dda4043d61a8e84484f7254017c59d8407bae",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 176,
        "name": "Liang Zhen",
        "email": "liang.zhen@intel.com",
        "username": "liangzhen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-01-06 15:41:37.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 5.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "a5901091247db67a3dec60c42f263950ebf05fb4",
